This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dominic Evan Dorn in court.  
Prosecuting attorney Katrina Voge appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm. 
Hearing held via Zoom.  Matter set for pretrial conference.  Defendant does not qualify for a public defender and would like to represent himself.  Court examined the defendant as to his capacity to represent himself and found he knowingly, voluntarily, intelligently waived his right to counsel. Case is adjourned to Br. 1.
Status conference scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY. 
No driving without a valid license. 
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Dominic Evan Dorn in court.  Prosecuting attorney Kimberly Dorice Schoepp in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 1.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 23, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Initial appearance on September 1, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
Defendant is Out-of-Custody. Court appearance in Out-Of-Custody Court, Room 221 Safety Building on 9/1/22 @ 1p
